ATTENTION PARENTS- Please complete the following form if you would like school meals delivered to your student(s) on home-based instruction days. Please note- only current students attending one of our schools are eligible for meal delivery (normal student meal prices will apply).

Responses are due by 5:00 pm on Thursday, September 3rd. Please complete one survey per family. In the instance of shared custody, only one parent needs to complete this form. Parents will need to communicate student's living schedule in advance with the bus driver or transportation supervisor. Meal delivery is only available on scheduled school days.

*Please note- students living in town will be provided with a designated pick-up site and time.

post_text:
ATTENTION PARENTS: Due to the circumstances of the COVID pandemic we have been placed in uncharted waters related to school. To help with this adjustment, we are looking for your input for student placement in either A or B groups. We are wanting to keep families together and work with your schedules as much as possible. "A" group will attend live on Monday and Tuesday. "B" group will attend live on Thursday and Friday. Wednesday is a student/parent contact, collaboration and deep clean facilities day. Distance learning would occur on the three alternating days your child is not at the school. We will try our best to place your child/children for the requested days, but may not be able to honor all requests. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact us via email and/or phone.

Please submit your responses by 5:00 pm on Monday, August 17th.

High School fall sport/activity meetings for parents & participants will be held on Tuesday, July 28th at the football field. We ask that you bring chairs to accommodate for social distancing. Please contact your coach if you are unable to attend.

6:00 pm - Cross country & Cheerleading

6:30 pm - Volleyball

7:00 pm - Football

SPORT PHYSICALS are to be completed and turned in prior to the first practice of the season. All incoming 7th/9th/11th grade students are required to have one completed as well as out of state transfer students and 8th/10th/12th grade students who did not complete one the previous year.

PSD285.ORG
2020 Fall Sport Parent/ Participant Meeting

We hope you understand that our “education landscape” is constantly changing due to the COVID-19 pandemic so we are being optimistic that all our plans will be able to go into place on schedule but we also are cautious knowing that these plans can change very quickly. We are providing you with a seven (7) question survey that looks at options and opportunities that can be/will be provided at the start of the school year. We are asking for you to return this survey by tomorrow, Thursday, July 16th. Thank you!

May 19 at 3:18 PM ·

PHS Class of 2020 Commencement Live Stream.

On Saturday, May 30, 2020, Mirror Up Imagery will be live streaming the Potlatch High School Class of 2020 Commencement Ceremonies for all who cannot be present to watch in person. We will be flying a drone (the ultimate social distancing tool) during the Graduation Parade in Downtown Potlatch at 10am on Facebook Live and then will be broadcasting the commencement ceremony at 11am from Potlatch High School football field via Youtube or Facebook Live depending on which works better. Links to the live streams will be provided just prior to the events. Please follow Mirror Up Imagery on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/Mirrorupimagery/
and Subscribe on Youtube to be notified of live videos and share with your friends and family.
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCJ40E5zMHQlUwVJV4oZZgTw

post_text:
From PHS Senior, Alyssa Hamburg- "THANK YOU to everyone that came out to donate. I really do appreciate everyone’s support. Due to having to take extra precautions in social distancing and keeping everyone safe, everyone had to wait way longer than expected, so I apologize for that.

After the blood drive, we had a total of 31 donors, which is 93 lives saved! So my goal was met in receiving a $2,000 STEM grant from both drives.

Again, THANK YOU to everyone that came out and donated, without your support and patience, I would not have been able to reach my goal!"
text:
From PHS Senior, Alyssa Hamburg- "THANK YOU to everyone that came out to donate. I really do appreciate everyone’s support. Due to having to take extra precautions in social distancing and keeping everyone safe, everyone had to wait way longer than expected, so I apologize for that.

After the blood drive, we had a total of 31 donors, which is 93 lives saved! So my goal was met in receiving a $2,000 STEM grant from both drives.

Again, THANK YOU to everyone that came out and donated, without your support and patience, I would not have been able to reach my goal!"

post_text: Congratulations to Olivia Wise and Josephine Pagel on a job well done at the North Idaho Science and Engineering Fair! Both students were recognized for their projects at this year's event. Olivia Wise received an Award for Most Outstanding ability and creativity in In Vitro Biology from the Society of In Vitro Biology. Josephine Pagel received Award from ASM Materials Education Foundation on Most Outstanding Exhibit in Materials Science, as well as a Silver medal in the microbiology and biomedical category. Way to go!
